DISTRIBUTION. SE 
<collectingCountry id="F37D7674FFA0FF95FEA1495D57E2F93A" box="[365,410,1663,1686]" name="Iran" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Iran</collectingCountry>
and SW 
<collectingCountry id="F37D7674FFA0FF95FDCE495C541DF93B" box="[514,613,1662,1687]" name="Pakistan" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD536E4FFA0FF95FF5B4981520CF973" blockId="44.[151,1436,1518,1940]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
DISTRIBUTION IN 
<collectingCountry id="F37D7674FFA0FF95FEAB498157E7F916" box="[359,415,1699,1722]" name="Iran" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">IRAN</collectingCountry>
. 
<figureCitation id="13512A61FFA0FF95FE7F49815460F910" box="[435,536,1699,1724]" captionStart="FIGURES 128–133. 128" captionStartId="93.[151,264,1557,1580]" captionTargetBox="[171,1416,213,1516]" captionTargetId="figure-79@93.[151,1436,193,1536]" captionTargetPageId="93" captionText="FIGURES 128–133. 128. Ablepharus pannonicus. 129. Chalcides ocellatus. 130. Eumeces schneiderii. Red symbols represent records of E. s. princeps, blue of E. s. zarudnyi and blue square denotes its type locality, violet question mark indicates dubious data for E. blythianus. 131. Eurylepis taeniolatus. 132. Ophiomorus blanfordii. 133. Ophiomorus brevipes." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4929775" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4929775/files/figure.png" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Fig. 132</figureCitation>
. Known with certainty only from the 
<typeStatus id="54D18846FFA0FF95FC2C49815268F917" box="[992,1040,1699,1723]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">type</typeStatus>
locality, although there are more mentions of this species but without exact locality data (
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B15FFA0FF95FCC049E455BCF973" author="Boulenger, G. A." box="[780,964,1734,1759]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" refId="ref47622" refString="Boulenger, G. A. (1887) Catalogue of the lizards in the British Museum (Natural History). Vol. III. Lacertidae, Gerrhosauridae, Scincidae, Anelytropidae, Dibamidae, Chamaeleontidae. Trustees of the British Museum, London, 575 pp." type="book" year="1887">Boulenger 1887</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B15FFA0FF95FC1C49E5521FF973" author="Werner, F." box="[976,1127,1734,1759]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="191 - 220" refId="ref67401" refString="Werner, F. (1917) Reptilien aus Persien (Provinz Fars). Verhandlungen der Zoologisch-Botanishen Gesellschaft in Wien, 67, 191 - 220." type="journal article" year="1917">Werner 1917</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD536E4FFA0FF95FF5B49C955F8F8A8" blockId="44.[151,1436,1518,1940]" box="[151,896,1771,1796]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
