<subSubSection id="C370656FFFA0FF95FF5B482D5476F8C3" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD536E4FFA0FF95FF5B482D5476F8C3" blockId="44.[151,1436,1518,1940]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
REMARKS. Boulenger in his original description used the spelling ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D67FFA0FF95FC4B482C558FF88B" authorityName="Boulenger" authorityYear="1887" box="[903,1015,1806,1831]" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Ophiomorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="blanfordii">
<emphasis id="B91EEAF6FFA0FF95FC4B482C558FF88B" box="[903,1015,1806,1831]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">blanfordii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ with a double ‘i’, hence the spelling ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D67FFA0FF95FF6C48115770F8E0" box="[160,264,1843,1868]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Acanthodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="blanfordi">
<emphasis id="B91EEAF6FFA0FF95FF6C48115770F8E0" box="[160,264,1843,1868]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">blanfordi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ used by many authors (
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B15FFA0FF95FDEC481154DFF8E0" author="Smith, M. A." box="[544,679,1843,1868]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" refId="ref65609" refString="Smith, M. A. (1935) The fauna of British India, including Ceylon and Burma. Reptilia and Amphibia. Vol. II. Sauria. Taylor and Francis, Ltd., Red Lion Court, Fleet Street, London, 440 pp. [Reprint Edition 1974, Today and Tomorrow's Printers and Publishers]" type="book" year="1935">Smith 1935</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B15FFA0FF95FD7848115596F8E0" author="Anderson, S. C. &amp; Leviton, A. E." box="[692,1006,1843,1868]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="499 - 534" refId="ref45420" refString="Anderson, S. C. &amp; Leviton, A. E. (1966 b) A review of the genus Ophiomorus with description of three new forms. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, 33, 499 - 534." type="journal article" year="1966">Anderson &amp; Leviton 1966b</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B15FFA0FF95FC36481152D2F8E0" author="Anderson, S. C." box="[1018,1194,1843,1868]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" refId="ref45318" refString="Anderson, S. C. (1999) The lizards of Iran. Society for the Study of Amphibians and Reptiles, Oxford, Ohio, 442 pp." type="book" year="1999">Anderson 1999</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B15FFA0FF95FB7A4811534DF8E0" author="Khan, M. S." box="[1206,1333,1843,1868]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" refId="ref56151" refString="Khan, M. S. (2006) Amphibians and Reptiles of Pakistan. Krieger Publishing Company, Malabar, Florida, 311 pp." type="book" year="2006">Khan 2006</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B15FFA0FF95FA8E48115702F8C3" author="Sindaco, R. &amp; Jeremcenko, V. K." pageId="44" pageNumber="45" refId="ref65138" refString="Sindaco, R. &amp; Jeremcenko, V. K. (2008) The reptiles of the Western Palearctic. 1. Annotated checklist and distributional atlas of the turtles, crocodiles, amphisbaenians and lizards of Europe, North Africa, Middle East and Central Asia. Monografie della Societas Herpetologica Italica, Edizioni Belvedere, 579 pp." type="book" year="2008">Sindaco &amp; Jeremčenko 2008</bibRefCitation>
) is incorrect.
</paragraph>
